    "body": "Why, why, _why_ does Truffle persist in hard-coding the solc version? Allowing users to manage this dependency would allow us to upgrade solc to avoid dangerous compiler errors as they arise without maintaining our own fork.  It would be as simple as putting `\"solc\": \"^0.4.25\"` instead of `\"solc\": \"0.4.25\"` in the package.json.",
